## 📡 POST-EXPLOITATION COMMANDS
Once a session is established, use these native Android tools:
- pm: Package Manager (e.g., pm list packages).
- am: Activity Manager (e.g., am start -n <package>/<activity>).
- auto_root: Attempt silent privilege escalation via Dirty Pipe/COW LPE.
- dump_sms: Exfiltrate all SMS messages from the inbox.
- dump_calls: Exfiltrate call logs (number, type, duration).
- dump_wifi: Extract stored WiFi SSIDs and passwords (Requires Root).
- dump_chrome: Harvest Chrome browser cookies and logins (Requires Root).
- dump_google_passwords: Extract GMS and System-synced credentials (Requires Root).
- find_cookies: Search for all application cookie databases (Requires Root).
- find_passwords: Search for all application password stores (Requires Root).
- screencap: Capture the device screen in real-time.

